fting. Now we did some on our Himalayan trip but it was pretty cold and the highest grade of rapids were a few Grade 2 and one Grade 3, so not the most riveting. Rafting on the Zambezi River beneath Victoria Falls is a little more challenging. The lowest rapids were Grade 3 and there were Grade 4 and 5 as well. Furthermore, the presence of crocodiles made falling out of the raft a bit more nerve raking. After a thorough safety briefing, we hit the river.&nbsp;&nbsp;We began with white water rafting. Now we did some on our Himalayan trip but it was pretty cold and the highest grade of rapids were a few Grade 2 and one Grade 3, so not the most riveting. Rafting on the Zambezi River beneath Victoria Falls is a little more challenging. The lowest rapids were Grade 3 and there were Grade 4 and 5 as well. Furthermore, the presence of crocodiles made falling out of the raft a bit more nerve raking. After a thorough safety briefing, we hit the river. &nbsp;The 13 sets of rapids managed to get everyone in our raft out at least once, I ended up out 3 times. On the grade 5, one famous wave hurled both Carlos and myself out of the raft. (I say ‘wave’ but it looked more like a tsunami to me!). For anyone heading to Victoria Falls, rafting is a must. That evening we did the tandem gorge swing despite being over the weight limit. It was AMAZING! Swinging on a 72m wire into an awe-inspiring gorge.</em></p></article></div><!-- /.container -->\n\n    	</div><!-- /.item -->\n\n    </div> <!-- end array--> ', '<li class=\"element layout ui-draggable ui-draggable-handle\" style=\"display: list-item; height: 131px; position: relative; left: 0px; top: 0px;\"><iframe src=\"builder_front/elements/layout_1_column.html\" scrolling=\"no\" frameborder=\"0\" id=\"ui-id-6\" style=\"background: url(&quot;builder_front/images/loading.gif&quot;) 50% 50% no-repeat rgb(255, 255, 255); height: 131px; width: 768px;\">&lt;iframe&gt;</iframe><div class=\"frameCover\" style=\"height: 131px; display: none;\